explanation: The solution uses a backtracking approach to generate all combinations of the given length. It starts by initializing an empty list to store the combinations and a StringBuilder to build each combination. The backtrack method is called recursively to generate all combinations. It appends each character to the StringBuilder and recursively calls itself until the desired length is reached. If the length is reached, the combination is added to the list. The next method returns the next combination in the list, and the hasNext method checks if there are more combinations left.

